      "content": "that's a great start, really hits the tone i'm looking for. can you expand on the part about meritocracy? i want to argue that the traditional idea of \"merit\" is actually kind of a fallacy when there's so much racial wealth disparity. how can i frame it so it sounds like the meritocracy argument is just a way to avoid addressing systemic issues?",
